parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause injuries, distractions, and accidents, and may also lead to unnecessary repair costs and downtime.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without a crash or impact
airbags deploy while the vehicle is stationary
airbags deploy while the vehicle is in motion
unexpected loud noise and sudden inflation of airbags.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the engine electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents. Additionally, the melting of wires can cause electrical shorts, leading to further damage to the vehicle's electrical system.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
the engine reaches high temperatures
wires are melted or damaged
the battery is drained or fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Battery failure can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the battery is dead
the battery is drained
the vehicle stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering wheel can cause loss of control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes loose or detached
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the steering wheel makes unusual noises
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Seat Position Memory Computer Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power seat position memory computer can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers, potentially leading to distractions while driving.
symptoms: The power seat memory function does not work
the seat does not return to its previously saved position
the seat adjustment buttons do not respond
the seat moves unexpectedly
error messages appear on the dashboard display.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel bearing can cause the wheel to seize, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Grinding or screeching noise from the wheel
vibration or shaking of the steering wheel
uneven tire wear
wheel lock-up or seizure
difficulty steering
pulling or drifting to one side.
